Kumba Iron Ore Says State Agrees Delay to Sishen Right, Bus. Day Reports

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-02-11T05:01:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/kumba-iron-ore-says-state-agrees-delay-to-sishen-right-bus-day-reports.html
  Kumba Iron Ore Ltd . said the
government’s Department of Mineral Resources has agreed to delay
the award of a partial mining right over its Sishen mine in
South Africa to Imperial Crown Trading until Kumba’s legal
challenge to an initial prospecting right is heard in August,
Johannesburg’s Business Day said, citing Vincent Uren, the
company’s chief financial officer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  